functioning of the car also form a bigger part of your safety on the roads.<\/p>\n<p>The features of car safety have two broad distinctions: Active and Passive. The active features are basically designed to reduce the car&#x2019;s physical damage. They reduce the likelihood of a crash. The active safety features include brakes,<\/p>\n<p>anti-lock braking systems, tire-pressure monitoring systems, and much more but the most important is the driver itself. The passive features try to reduce the risk of damage done to the passengers in the event of a crash. The passive safety features include seatbelts, airbags, crumple zones, etc.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_50 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-transparent ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/safest-cars-in-india-2022\/#Top_5_Safest_Cars_You_Can_Buy_in_India\" title=\"Top 5 Safest Cars You Can Buy in India\">Top 5 Safest Cars You Can Buy in India<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/safest-cars-in-india-2022\/#1_Tata_Nexon\" title=\"1) Tata Nexon\">1) Tata Nexon<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/safest-cars-in-india-2022\/#2_Mahindra_XUV_300\" title=\"2) Mahindra XUV 300\">2) Mahindra XUV 300<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/safest-cars-in-india-2022\/#3_Tata_Altroz\" title=\"3) Tata Altroz\">3) Tata Altroz<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc